UPDATE: Seems all the different Android flavors are coming home to roost!    On my DroidX with v.2.3.4 (gingerbread) from Dec. 2011, the new update of ScanBizCard Premium 1.51 generated several camera conflicts: 1. takes photo / doesn't orient or scan, 2. takes photo / goes back to intro page, 3. retrieve photo / goes back to intro page, 4. won't email photo of card.  If your handset also has these symptoms, you'll understand why I wrote here that it ah... sucks!  But within minutes the ScanBizCard team reacted to my negative post here and to tech support first by email, then with a call!   They directed me to "Please touch Settings on the main page, then uncheck Use Device Camera (or vice-versa)."  I also rebooted the phone, and though it'll need more testing, it all seems to be working fine now!    So I've upped my rating from 1 star to 4, cause this app maker has a good product, wants it to be great, listens to user feedback, and does something about it in minutes.  Thank YOU, ScanBizCard!

I scan using Samsung Galaxy S II because of the awesome camera. Then scan card on phone and then it automatically syncs to web site. This allows viewing of card via Samsung phone, Ipad or PC. I also can update info which is then available instantly by phone, Ipad and PC. Suggestions for improvement: Allow account tags which pop up with must know info every time contact accessed.

Fantastic app for anyone who wants to load business cards on the go. Built in LinkedIn request capability makes it even sweeter. Support is fast, friendly and personal (and only occasionally needed). I rarely buy apps, but it's worth it to get the Premium version of this one because it's simply loaded with features and options. I use it especially when I meet a lot of people at conferences and need to follow up efficiently with them - take a photo of the card (and the backside if I want), 30 second check to see the app has scanned the card info correctly, save it to my Google and Outlook accounts and send a LinkedIn request if appropriate. Eliminates the need for secretarial assistance with my cards. Eliminates the need to carry them with me, since I can access the original image through the app.  Simply brilliant.
